ETF Recommendations:      - For broad market exposure: VTI (Vanguard Total Stock Market ETF)      - For international diversification: VXUS (Vanguard Total International Stock ETF)      - For bonds (if needed): BND (Vanguard Total Bond Market ETF)    3. Tax Implications:      - ETFs generally generate fewer capital gains distributions than mutual funds.      - You�ll only owe taxes when you sell shares (long-term vs. short-term rates apply).    I�m available Thursday at 2:00 PM�does that work? I�ll send a calendar invite.    Best,   Mia    ---  Subject: RE: Exploring ETF Investment Options     Hi Mia,    Thanks for the detailed response! I generally recommend limiting sector ETFs to 5�10% of your portfolio unless you have strong conviction. We can discuss this further tomorrow.    Talk soon,   Mia
